Author: ver_User#6608
Content:
In particular when it's based off one trendline and basic of basic support/resistance. Even gorillas can spot that stuff. 

The other day I saw someone post "IN 36 HOURS EURUSD WILL BE AT 1.15XX" so I said to him, probable, maybe, not WILL. He said, "SEE MY PAST ANALYSIS". 

36 hours later, euro was at 1.143...

upside seems likely, but time is the hardest factor in charting IMO, especially when making long term lows/highs or corrections.
